One additional note: the source-tag, when used, only shows the path the 
crawler actually took to discover a URI -- not necessarily the shortest 
path.

(All sorts of site, network, queueing, and policy/politeness delays mean 
that some paths have been followed many hops while others far fewer, and 
the source-tag that appears in the crawl.log, when using this feature, 
is only set when a URI is first discovered-and-queued.)

